# Code Quality

## Style

- async/await for asynchronous operations
- JSDoc on public methods
- Use `this.log.*` — never `console.log`
- Tabs, double quotes (see `prettier.config.mjs`)
- ESLint via `@iobroker/eslint-config` — run `npm run lint` after every change

## Resource cleanup

Use adapter-core interval helpers; clear in `onUnload()` and always call `callback()`:

```javascript
onReady() {
  this.updateInterval = this.setInterval(() => this.poll(), this.config.interval * 1000);
}

onUnload(callback) {
  try {
    if (this.updateInterval) {
      this.clearInterval(this.updateInterval);
      this.updateInterval = undefined;
    }
    callback();
  } catch (error) {
    this.log.error(`Error during unloading: ${error.message}`);
    callback();
  }
}
```

## Error handling

- Wrap async/API work in try/catch; log errors, do not crash the adapter
- Use adapter log levels: error, warn, info, debug
- Handle network failures gracefully; set `info.connection` state accordingly

## HTTP

- **Preferred:** native `node:https` module (already used in adapter)
- **Avoid:** axios, request, or other HTTP libraries

## Dependencies

- Use `npm ci` in CI; commit `package-lock.json` with `package.json`
- Use `@iobroker/adapter-core`; avoid deprecated packages
- Update dependencies in separate PRs only
- Prefer built-in Node.js modules where possible
